commit_message:
Delete enabled argument from region

Region has an 'enabled' argument. But Identity V3 API doesn't
provide enabled attribute of region.
This patch deletes 'enabled' argument from region.

Change-Id: Id86c620d33408860d99bcf9c00f737870092c0fc
Closes-Bug: #1507838

commit_message:
Fix comment of create_keystone_accounts()

1) Group does not add user in create_keystone_accounts().
2) It's rather 'Project' than 'Tenant' in the comments.
This patch fixes comment of create_keystone_accounts().

Change-Id: Ibc0824fd9c13a91ff28c8b2edc1129d249a01478

Update development environment set up doc

Since install_venv.py and with_venv.sh under tools directory
were deleted, updated development environment set up doc to
use tox for building virtual environments.

commit_message:
Update volume API v1 and v2 to make these changes

- Spell-check and remove passive voice from api-site
- Renamed api-ref/src/wadls/volume-api/src/v1/api_samples
  and api-ref/src/wadls/volume-api/src/v2/api_samples
  to .../samples
- Renamed code samples using this naming convention:
  <resource>-<action>-request.json or <resource>-<action>-response.json.
  For example, volume-create-request.json and volume-create-response.json.
- Removed unused code samples
- Made method names consistent throughout - use list<resource> for list
  operations, show<resource> for show operations, and so on.
- Changed csapi:uuid -> csapi:UUID

Change-Id: I61f33e093c2ec882680d85e9cb3f7c450107496e
Partial-Bug: #1521244

commit_message:
/NetworkDriver.CreateEndpoint cleanup

Add logic to search for port created by ipam and remove subnet creation
logic. Now subnets are created using IPv4Data and IPv6Data in
/NetworkDriver.CreateNetwork

Change-Id: I675bc7133b714cc18a7ee57a8431a8795fffe75e
Closes-Bug: #1521111

(1 comment)'}, {'account_id': 14352, 'date': '2015-11-27 19:42:38.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

(7 comments)

That was one long review! Thanks a lot for the submission Vikas!

Apart of all the fundamental questions I raised in the comments, shouldn't this
patch also remove the port creation from the current controller and the check
of the extension in the kuryr server (as it is already done in kuryr_ipam
server).

Of course, that would mean that kuryr only works with kuryr ipam driver.
I haven't made up my mind completely on that. I'd appreciate people comments on
that. For me it would mean:

Good
====

allow us to simplify the implementation of the kuryr
server

Bad
===

Remove users choice to use the builtin ipam driver with kuryr."}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-11-28 05:56:02.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

(11 comments)

Thanks for reviewing it Toni, Please find my comments inline.

1. On "shouldn't this patch also remove the port creation from the current controller" :

ipam-driver is creating a port, fetching allocated ip and the "deleting" the port. So current controller(network-driver) should still be creating a port. Ofcourse, it is not a good approach to recreate port in CreateEndpoint rather using already created by ipam, but i could not find a way about how to refer to this ipam created port from within CreateEndpoint.

In ipam's "request_address" api, libnetwork is not providing any endpointid so that ipam could that this port and later it could be refered back from CreateEndpoint using same tag.

With current changes, users still can use built-in ipam.


2. On "check of the extension in the kuryr server", Yes this can be removed as subnetpools will be used by ipam now. 


I would prefer to wait for one or two days more to get review comments for other reviewers also before updating next patch-set. WDYT?'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-11-28 06:02:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

s/so that ipam could that this port/so that ipam could tag this port'}, {'account_id': 11343, 'date': '2015-11-28 07:02:05.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8: Code-Review-1

(2 comments)

Thanks Vikas for the work.

I think that the problem about port deletion/creation start from the fact that this IPAM implementation is running on a different process.

I personally think they should run together (i assume this is possible) and then its easier to synchronise if port is already created/deleted.

What is the reason to keep them separated?'}, {'account_id': 11343, 'date': '2015-11-28 07:03:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

And if we still want to keep them separated, i would not do the port create/delete but rather add logic to see if a port is already created in the current Kuryr controller'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-11-28 09:16:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

(2 comments)

@Gal,

1>> On why running these two as seperate processes:

Honestly, I am unable to come-up with any concrete reason. Going by Banix's opinion[1], just because these two are logically different entities/components/modules, thought of running seperate servers as better choice. If consensus is reached to run them as single, small refactoring will be needed.

2. On avoiding port-delete:

Will try to use "Data" from request_address response form,[2], to pass port-id to network-driver. 

[1] http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/meetings/kuryr/2015/kuryr.2015-10-19-15.00.log.html at 15:44:51  

[2] https://github.com/docker/libnetwork/blob/master/docs/ipam.md#requestaddress'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-11-28 12:30:50.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

@Gal and Toni,

I will fix this current port-create/port-delete and add logic in network driver to fetch the same port created by ipam in next patch set.


Thanks
Vikas'}, {'account_id': 12069, 'date': '2015-11-30 03:00:19.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

(6 comments)

Thanks for doing this Vikas. This patch looks big enough already and some APIs are not just implemented. IMHO, we should start by the introduction of the small IPAM driver which doesn't have the implementations but only interfaces, and then we can add each API with unit tests gradually.

Regarding the driver, I think it's better to have the network driver and the ipam driver together as "Kuryr" practically. They're different entities in libnetwork model but they're not in Neutron. Separating the IPAM driver from Kuryr would not have much advantages but introduces additional complexities. If we don't want to use the IPAM driver of Kuryr, we can just omit "--ipam-driver" option when we create networks. Then the APIs are implemented but never used. But honestly I can't bring the use case where we would use the non-Kuryr IPAM driver once we implement it correctly.'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-11-30 05:30:33.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

(4 comments)

Thanks Taku. Will be updating patch set addressing review comments.'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-11-30 06:03:41.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 9.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-30 06:06:11.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Verified+1

- gate-kuryr-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/42/248042/9/check/gate-kuryr-python27/7a37cb2/ : SUCCESS in 2m 03s'}, {'account_id': 12069, 'date': '2015-11-30 10:53:26.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

(7 comments)'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-11-30 11:14:06.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

(3 comments)

Thanks Taku, will update.'}, {'account_id': 12069, 'date': '2015-12-01 09:59:53.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9: Code-Review-1

(8 comments)

More comments would follow but I just flush my current buffer.'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-12-02 09:31:52.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 10.'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-12-02 09:33:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 9:

Please find my comments inline.

- gate-kuryr-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/42/248042/10/check/gate-kuryr-pep8/2ae7c91/ : FAILURE in 1m 54s
- gate-kuryr-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/42/248042/10/check/gate-kuryr-docs/b3647bc//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 1m 57s
- gate-kuryr-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/42/248042/10/check/gate-kuryr-python27/2d9e64e/ : FAILURE in 2m 09s
- gate-install-dsvm-kuryr-nv http://logs.openstack.org/42/248042/10/check/gate-install-dsvm-kuryr-nv/dbe70d8/ : SUCCESS in 13m 33s (non-voting)'}, {'account_id': 12069, 'date': '2015-12-02 11:15:51.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 10: Code-Review-1

(15 comments)

Most of the code for the configuration, the utilities and the server of the IPAM driver is duplicated with the one of the network driver. That's why I think it's better to put the IPAM driver and the network driver together in the same process. We could use the default IPAM but as we discussed, it's not the legitimately done and it accidentally works. So I can say Kuryr network driver can't work without Kuryr IPAM driver and I don't think it'd be the problem to make them a single process.

I'd also want to see some more test cases for IPv6 but they makes this patch even bigger. So I'd like to see this patch is split into few patches, for instance for each API endpoint."}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-12-02 16:25:00.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10:

@Taku


Makes sense. Will split this patch set into multiple review request and making network driver and ipam running as same process. By tomorrow will be submitting these changes.'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-12-03 11:23:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 10: Workflow-1

(1 comment)

Have split this patch into multiple small patches for the sake of review convenience. Here is the series start point https://review.openstack.org/#/c/252796/'}, {'account_id': 15967, 'date': '2015-12-14 07:03:49.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

Copied to https://review.openstack.org/#/c/256205/'}]

commit_message:
Add _show_resource to EncryptedVolumeType

Currently cinder doesn't support to_dict
method for it's resources, so we should add
override _show_resource method for
Cinder::EncryptedVolumeType.

Change-Id: Id9cd115f7029864b9af241eb00c086e9b9f5dd22
Closes-bug: #1520473
(cherry picked from commit 5799a0fcde257ccafa5e6dd4554ee79f6a6e85c5)

commit_message:
Update Image service API v1 and v2 to spellcheck and make other changes

- Remove passive voice from api-site
- Renamed api-ref/src/wadls/image-api/src/v1/api_samples
  to .../samples
- Renamed code samples using this naming convention:
  <resource>-<action>-request.json or <resource>-<action>-response.json.
  For example, volume-create-request.json and volume-create-response.json.
- Removed unused code samples
- Made method names consistent throughout - use list<resource> for list
  operations, show<resource> for show operations, and so on.
- csapi:uuid -> csapi:UUID

Change-Id: I78189bbab4f50b46c4c146abe5e95bede379dda7
Partial-Bug: #1521244

[glossary] Small corrections in glossary terms list

1.) Delete the duplicate 'API' glossary term. The deleted term
is used in install-guide so made changes in install-guide

2.) The mitaka summit is over. so changed the description of
mitaka accordingly

commit_message:
Bump python-openstackclient version to 2.0.0

Version 2.0.0 is needed by python-heatclient to support their
openstackclient plugin support.

Release change: Ic4eb74e35a6c301e8e6be238c7d5196603236564

Change-Id: Ib778047f44bcfc4f5528aa38599366d240367842

commit_message:
Don't remove role assignment if no change

If there is no change of role assignment, do not update.

Change-Id: I4f1c89b265e2cbeacc9f110bd1e27d5c9234f714
Closes-Bug: #1522310
(cherry picked from commit 0500ac6765cc3cd5ebc01ff5b13f2c0ac01c96cd)

commit_message:
re-implement thread safe fnmatch

fnmatch is not thread safe for versions <= 2.7.9. We have used
it in some projects without any lock for concurrency scenario. This patch
re-implements a thread safe fnmatch which is very similar to standard
nmatch.

Change-Id: I610ffcdf58d1590b8e0c0faefd8832563b33ab30
ref: https://bugs.python.org/issue23191

Some of the glance storage backend drivers require root privileges.
For example, to implement upload/download into the cinder backend,
we need to manage block devices (such as FC or iSCSI volumes).
This patch allows them to use oslo.rootwrap as "glance-rootwrap"
command.

Command filters for glance-rootwrap will be contained in
the glance_store repositry, so that the changes to the filters
can be provided in the same patches for driver changes that
requires new commands to be executed with root privileges.

commit_message:
Importing oslo.rootwrap into Glance

Some of the glance storage backend drivers like cinder require
root priveleges. This patch allows them to use oslo.rootwrap
as the glance-rootwrap command.
Command filters for glance-rootwrap are contained in glance_store
repositry as they are provided by the drivers.

Change-Id: I2a6183440d107afdb4e9bf087282e8604a9eea93
Partially Implements: blueprint cinder-store-upload-download

Commented in lines, need more opinions.'}, {'account_id': 8246, 'date': '2015-12-14 02:35:23.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 2:

(2 comments)

While in general I'm okay with the removal of 'return None' or replacing 'return None' with 'return', I'm not a big fan of this change.

My primary concern is about code readability. For example, you have a function that may and may not return some objects. When you do have valid object/status to return, you can write 'return something'. When you don't have things to return and you are not raising exceptions, you can do either 'return' or 'return None'. Both are correct from syntax or semantics perspective. I'd prefer the second one when a function does return something in other paths. It reminds me (or other developers) that this function is supposed to return something, though not in the current path."}, {'account_id': 6763, 'date': '2015-12-14 04:10:55.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

HI Qiming, thanks for your detailed explanations, i got the tips.'}, {'account_id': 6763, 'date': '2015-12-14 05:51:50.000000000', 'content': "Abandoned

by Qiming

While in general I'm okay with the removal of 'return None' or replacing 'return None' with 'return', I'm not a big fan of this change.
My primary concern is about code readability. For example, you have a function that may and may not return some objects. When you do have valid object/status to return, you can write 'return something'. When you don't have things to return and you are not raising exceptions, you can do either 'return' or 'return None'. Both are correct from syntax or semantics perspective. I'd prefer the second one when a function does return something in other paths. It reminds me (or other developers) that this function is supposed to return something, though not in the current path."}]

commit_message:
Add workaround to fix centos-binary-deploy gate

The RDO nova package is missing a dependency on oslo-policy and this is
breaking our centos-binary-deploy gate. Install the missing package in
nova-base until the issue is fixed upstream.

Change-Id: Iece7edd754c6f173635b0e0c437a998f3b9492d3
Closes-Bug: #1525502

commit_message:
Deprecated tox -downloadcache option removed

Caching is enabled by default from pip version 6.0

More info:
https://testrun.org/tox/latest/config.html#confval-downloadcache=path
https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#caching

commit_message:
Remove import of unnecessary modules from Horizon

Manila UI tests import modules with test data for lots of projects.
It is unnecessary and should be removed.
One of such unnecessary modules was removed from Horizon and unit tests
are broken because of it. So, remove breaking one and all other unused.

Change-Id: Ic121ac52d261b1f4eb972a0075cd3a09883fb100
Closes-Bug: #1524735
(cherry picked from commit ef8bf7bcb9aee5355f998aeb62f674ad9f12e9eb)

commit_message:
Delete python bytecode before every test run

Because python creates pyc files during tox runs, certain
changes in the tree, like deletes of files, or switching
branches, can create spurious errors.

Change-Id: I27887fe68e84ee621c9e8687908d1ba1818a151f
Closes-Bug: #1368661

commit_message:
Remove quotation checking of Etag value in Swift SLO GET

Based on swift API documentation, Etag value should not get quoted.
This patch removes quotation checking of ETag value in slo GET,
to remove quotation process in Swift.

Change-Id: I81bb9cd9b70470c7940b7257b1319ede8d708be5

subject: Unquote etag value in getting SLO/DLO
messages:
[{'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2015-11-26 04:22:55.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 1.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-26 05:15:39.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified-1

Build failed (check pipeline).  For information on how to proceed, see http://docs.openstack.org/infra/manual/developers.html#automated-testing

- gate-swift-pep8 http://logs.openstack.org/45/250145/1/check/gate-swift-pep8/0c56f90/ : SUCCESS in 1m 52s
- gate-swift-docs http://docs-draft.openstack.org/45/250145/1/check/gate-swift-docs/75d3bd0//doc/build/html/ : SUCCESS in 3m 01s
- gate-swift-python27 http://logs.openstack.org/45/250145/1/check/gate-swift-python27/8c610d3/ : SUCCESS in 9m 17s

- gate-tempest-dsvm-full http://logs.openstack.org/45/250145/1/check/gate-tempest-dsvm-full/5a6e926/ : FAILURE in 45m 03s
- gate-grenade-dsvm http://logs.openstack.org/45/250145/1/check/gate-grenade-dsvm/b1a642a/ : SUCCESS in 41m 12s
- gate-swift-dsvm-functional http://logs.openstack.org/45/250145/1/check/gate-swift-dsvm-functional/400c30b/ : SUCCESS in 28m 18s'}, {'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2015-11-26 05:56:58.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Tempest seems to check if etag is quoted in SLO, and that causes the failure in test. 

I should commit a patch to tempest and somehow set relations with this patch.'}, {'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2015-11-30 01:08:51.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 2.'}, {'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2015-11-30 01:12:12.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 3.'}, {'account_id': 330, 'date': '2015-11-30 01:20:04.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

Oh my. This is a tough one.

One the one hand, we've got known inconsistency in our API now. The RFC says to use the quotes, but we've already rejected that because of clients that break if we add quotes.

I'd love to see consistency, but will clients break if we remove the *LO quotes at this point?

On the other hand, if clients are handling quotes now anyway with *LOs, then maybe we can move to API consistency by adding quotes to regular objects. Maybe clients have learned how to properly read the ETag values.

Options:

 * leave the inconsistent API as-is
 * remove quotes from *LOs
 * add quotes to regular objects

I'll add this as an agenda item to the next meeting (Wednesdays at 2100UTC)"}, {'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2015-11-30 01:20:29.000000000', 'content': 'Uploaded patch set 4.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-30 01:33:15.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Verified-1

This change depends on a change that failed to merge.'}, {'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2015-11-30 03:18:23.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 4:

As I talked at IRC, I'll wait until we decide the way to go.

I think adding a new option to enable/disable quotation is another solution (to allow clients which need quoted etag in SLO/DLO), but I don't know if it is a good way."}, {'account_id': 330, 'date': '2015-12-02 22:45:40.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 4: Code-Review-2

Discussed today in the meeting: http://eavesdrop.openstack.org/meetings/swift/2015/swift.2015-12-02-21.02.log.html#l-239

As a result, adding a -2. This would change the API in such a way as to break clients.'}, {'account_id': 9816, 'date': '2015-12-14 04:09:26.000000000', 'content': 'Abandoned

@John OK, so I abandon this patch.'}]

commit_message:
Unquote etag value in getting SLO/DLO

This patch unquotes etag value in getting SLO/DLO, besed on the api
document which says "etag value should not be quoted", and recovers
the consistency in v1 API, which has its etag value unquoted.

Change-Id: I37f898324c4ae633d7bb5824f661750ed0efcb73
Depends-On: I81bb9cd9b70470c7940b7257b1319ede8d708be5
Closes-Bug: 1520037

Deprecated tox -downloadcache option removed

Caching is enabled by default from pip version 6.0

More info:
https://testrun.org/tox/latest/config.html#confval-downloadcache=path
https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#caching

[{'created': '2015-12-04 07:39:34.000000000', 'message': "fix external net always can be seen for rbac-network

Since rbac-network is introduced, a network should only be seen
by other tenant users if network is shared or network owner
create rbac rules for them to access.

But currently, for a external network, it still can be seen by
other tenant users without shared and rbac access rules.
Method _network_filter_hook in external_net_db make this happened,
for it helps external networks always not been filtered in
_single_model_query when then later one is called to query network
model.

For _single_model_query, its other inner filters are based on tenant_id
and *shared*, it doesn't make sense to make external net so special
always not to be filtered. So _network_filter_hook seems no need in
_single_model_query.

For _union_model_query, there seems no place will use ExternalNetwork
as a part of union query, where we may concern _network_filter_hook
will singly take effect.

So it make sense to remove _network_filter_hook from registered
_model_query_hooks.

This patch is going to fix external network always been seen issue and
clean _model_query_hooks.

Closes-Bug: #1522709

commit_message:
fix external net always can be seen for rbac-network

Since rbac-network is introduced, a network should only be seen
by other tenant users if network is shared or network owner
create rbac rules for them to access.

But currently, for a external network, it still can be seen by
other tenant users without shared and rbac access rules.
Method _network_filter_hook in external_net_db make this happened,
for it helps external networks always not been filtered in
_single_model_query when then later one is called to query network
model.

For _single_model_query, its other inner filters are based on tenant_id
and *shared*, it doesn't make sense to make external net so special
always not to be filtered. So _network_filter_hook seems no need in
_single_model_query.

For _union_model_query, there seems no place will use ExternalNetwork
as a part of union query, where we may concern _network_filter_hook
will singly take effect.

So it make sense to remove _network_filter_hook from registered
_model_query_hooks.

This patch is going to fix external network always been seen issue and
clean _model_query_hooks.

Change-Id: I90592f7e0322fb68ed191d5e31ee1a2162b49e18
Closes-Bug: #1522709

commit_message:
Add FSM.is_stable() method

This adds an FSM.is_stable(state) method which returns True if the
state is stable and False otherwise. Invalid states will cause an
exception to be raised.

Change-Id: Ic6a3c937be9370477fdb1fe2c462f6672497f838

commit_message:
Remove keystoneclient.middleware

The code has been moved to the new keystonemiddleware project and
keystone.middleware was deprecated since Juno. It's time to drop it in
Mitaka.

Remove the directory keystoneclient/middleware/.

Remove test_auth_token_middleware.py, test_memcache_crypt.py and
test_s3_token_middleware.py in keystoneclient/tests/unit/.

Remove the create_middleware_cert shell function from
examples/pki/gen_pki.sh. And remove the call from
examples/pki/run_all.sh.

Remove netaddr, pycrypto and WebOb test dependencies, only needed to
test the removed middleware.

Closes-Bug: #1449066
Change-Id: Iedd6887dcde62177d37e1e1988ed72bcb59c05f6

commit_message:
Make consistent usage of mock.patch decorators

The usage of @mock.patch.object vs @patch.object was inconsistent, this
fixes this inconsistency with a preference for @mock.patch.object.

This patch also contains clean up of unnecessary "with mock.patch.."
code and replaces it with a more readable decorator.

Change-Id: If4f10a5de568e4bd89fbed8ae57699e5282d87a1

After a few new features being added into drivers,
we found it hard to maintain the code. For further
working, we need to refactor our code. The work
contains the following:
1. Define a new class, named HuaweiConf, to parse
xml config file. We used an external xml file to

commit_message:
Huawei: Refactor driver for the second time

After a few new features being added into drivers,
we found it hard to maintain the code. For further
working, we need to refactor our code. The work
contains the following:
1. Define a new class, named HuaweiConf, to parse
xml config file. We used an external xml file to
store SAN info. But we do config parsing anywhere
in our code, even two different functions do the
same parsing.
2. Adjust some function structures.
3. Rename some functions & variables.

DocImpact
Implements: blueprint refactor-huawei-driver

Change-Id: Ica34f630241d7d58ac6be8020a4d827643c23ad6

commit_message:
Avoid tox 2.3.0

As https://bitbucket.org/hpk42/tox/issues/294 , tox 2.3.0 contains
a regression issue and a lot of gate jobs are being failed now.
This patch adds tox to global-requirements.txt for avoiding the tox
release.

Change-Id: I88cffc321cfa91fba4516f9def5d548084d64d97
Related-Bug: #1525352

commit_message:
Fix swap_volume for case without migration

Fix swap_volume so that even when a volume-migration does not
occur, the volumes don't get stuck in "attaching" and "detaching".
Previously the swap_volume was changed in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/101932 and
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/101933 to move the final
attach and detach logic to Cinder, however those changes only fix
the migration path.  This change calls Cinder's "attach" and "detach"
for the non-migration path to update the volumes' states.

Change-Id: I242c2c7c4a7197bbce04d0b3d75688f989ea1fd5
Closes-Bug: #1489744
(cherry picked from commit dc777f1dc736b01b8f8eec58972230d30b3074f6)

Nice work!  This looks right, though tempest hasn't finished yet.

Implementing remote-group has been a pain...

I just thought of something else, too.  Is remote-group supposed to work for ports not all on the same Neutron network?  If so, our implementation is broken for that, too.  We refer to ports by name, which only works for ports on the same OVN logical switch.  If they're on a different OVN logical switch, we'll have to switch to matching on IP addresses."}, {'account_id': 11762, 'date': '2015-12-11 19:52:49.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1:

Oh man, that is even more painful (translate to IPs). Thanks for bringing this up. I think it is worth looking into support from OVN itself for remote_group.

In OVN, it may utilize metadata to improve efficiency, although we would have more obstacles to solve. But overall I believe it would be better to handle in OVN than in plugin.

Before the complete support, I would suggest to define what to be supported for now in plugin and have it work properly within that scope/limitation.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-12-11 20:14:30.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

[{'created': '2015-12-11 19:01:43.000000000', 'message': "Fix update_port for security group change when remote_group involved

When there are security group changes, update_port doesn't work
properly: if there are security rules with remote-group, the acls
related to other port of that remote-group not updated for the
group membership change. This patch fixes the problem.

Closes-bug: 1525360

commit_message:
Fix update_port for security group change when remote_group involved

When there are security group changes, update_port doesn't work
properly: if there are security rules with remote-group, the acls
related to other port of that remote-group not updated for the
group membership change. This patch fixes the problem.

Closes-bug: 1525360

Change-Id: I5cf13fcbbc12539d99d9cd034a595f231b96372c

commit_message:

commit_message:
Use libs for liberty branch

Liberty devstack prevents force disabling services in localrc
This commit https://review.openstack.org/#/c/233106/2 fixed thi problem
but id doesn't exists in liberty devstack. So, because on Murano CI
workers we shouldn't enable neutron, we can't use plugin, because plugin
override localrc settings.

This commit moves liberty branch to libs-way installation.

Change-Id: Ide09e4226f5580184398b99473cb1ecfeb6542b6
Closes-Bug: #1524391

commit_message:
Add descriptions for by default admin only field.

Some fields such as OS-EXT-SRV-ATTR:host by default only
returned when the caller is admin, we need tell API user
about that.

Change-Id: I6021def80ffeceb30bd1b5c2ccfb5576662ceaac
Partial-Bug: #1515222

commit_message:
Improve readability of Horizon Packaging doc

Include various changes for readability. Make bulleted list parallel.
Shorten long sentences. In some cases include articles and clarify
subject in sentences. Spell out "for example." Eliminate redundant
words / phrases. Per Matthias's recommendation, shuffle order of topics
and create two sections to focus first on general packaging principles,
and then Horizon specifics.

Change-Id: Ic864dd926d723c6dc9749249655ae2e7d08ed225
Co-Authored-By: Matthias Runge <mrunge@redhat.com>
Closes-Bug: #1516986

commit_message:
Explicitly use asyncio protocol for websockets

The new default for txaio (dependency of autobahn) requires that you
specify how you want websocket connections to be managed (asyncio or
twisted) and raises an exception if you don't make a choice.

(cherry picked from commit ae7c7ff5afac3cafcf0ddea955a1dbeb13e4ddf4)

Conflicts:
	zaqar/transport/websocket/protocol.py

commit_message:
Deprecated tox -downloadcache option removed

Caching is enabled by default from pip version 6.0

More info:
https://testrun.org/tox/latest/config.html#confval-downloadcache=path
https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#caching

Change-Id: I8f9604584700276079fe5b51cfedffc820411b77

commit_message:
Pass environment variables of proxy to tox

When a development environment is under a proxy, tox is failed even if
environment variables of the proxy are set.

This patch fixes this problem.

Change-Id: I62c537aecc0a706afe048427a96b98a51abfc26b
Closes-bug: #1524824

Deprecated tox -downloadcache option removed

Caching is enabled by default from pip version 6.0

More info:
https://testrun.org/tox/latest/config.html#confval-downloadcache=path
https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#caching

commit_message:
add check for genisoimage

This adds a check for the fallback image creation tool and fails the
run if neither mkisofs and genisoimage are not found.

Change-Id: Ide6cf68e378fb7e5823edb9b8aca88bbd8874d60

commit_message:
pyudev exception has changed for from_device_file

Now pyudev raises DeviceNotFoundByFileError which does not inherit
from EnvironmentError, so our 'except' block in hardware.py no longer
catch the exception. It broke unit tests, but it can also potentially
break the deploy.

This patch updates hardware.py to catch both old a new exceptions.

Change-Id: Iaefd6089f6f766a241054d8e132b2f3098c8130d
Closes-Bug: #1522756
(cherry picked from commit 2fc6ce22f8b531d33bb3d7f7876dd42276231797)

Update ironic.conf.sample by applying the bug fix #1522841

This patch updates and removes obsoleted config parameters in
ironic.conf.sample with updates of keystonemiddleware is 4.0.0 and
oslo.messaging 3.1.0.

commit_message:
Cleanup XML from Networking API

Networking API no longer supports XML.
'API versions' in Networking API v2.0 and  'Extensions' in
Networking API v2.0 extensions are the remaining ones and
this commit removes them.

Change-Id: Ide2ddde05518e4560cf44acd9ca5af54621dacfc
Closes-Bug: #1525353

commit_message:
devstack: Avoid relying on Q_AGENT=openvswitch for ML2

Move a few functions from devstack/midonet/functions to
devstack/functions so that we don't need to use them
from openvswitch_agent.

Also, tweak the sample config so that devstack doesn't pull
openvswitch_agent.

Closes-Bug: #1524718
Change-Id: I8de30259041627c6866e0e42fa1f2cf2149fa787

commit_message:
Deprecated tox -downloadcache option removed

Caching is enabled by default from pip version 6.0

More info:
https://testrun.org/tox/latest/config.html#confval-downloadcache=path
https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#caching

Change-Id: I1778135d68a4bf96da3a0c0e4660172d1f13d16b

commit_message:
Pass environment variables of proxy to tox

When a development environment is under a proxy, tox is failed even if
environment variables of the proxy are set.

This patch fixes this problem.
Closes-Bug: #1525115

Change-Id: I9a870f21a1eef9983f1988d10c32366085ff88c6

commit_message:
Storwize: add config option to control flash copy rate

When creating a flash copy of a vdisk during a clone
or a snapshot operation the svcinfo mkfcmap operation
allows the specification of a copy rate for the flash copy.
The default copy rate is 50. The issue with 50 is it not
always an acceptable default copy rate for a particular
operator. Some operators want it slower but some want to
increase the default copy rate.

Adding a configuration option storwize_svc_flashcopy_rate
to allow an operator to specify the default flash copy
rate to be used when starting a vdisk flash copy on a
clone or snapshot operation.

DocImpact

Change-Id: Iffa50cf934f5d340a1f24ed3cfea8381b6dd6630
Closes-Bug: 1517185

commit_message:
Fix inappropriate uses about eventlet.Timeout

In storlet_runtime.py, there are some codes which generate a Timeout
with string as its argument though Timeout requires timeout value.

Change-Id: Id44a8544a2bc2d49d37d2a86c72f3c1a0a872265

commit_message:
Mark LBaaS v2 API as stable and LBaaS v1 API as deprecated

Neutron Liberty release note says:
The LBaaS V2 API is no longer experimental. It is now stable.
The LBaaS V1 API is marked as deprecated and is planned to be removed
in a future release. Going forward, the LBaaS V2 API should be used.

Change-Id: I0cc2349acbbf02845670f2e13f1d56659722c8d9
Closes-Bug: #1525567

As Sakai-san said on https://review.openstack.org/#/c/242901/ , 203 seems intentional for a cached proxy.

If a proxy is not trusted on SSL like PoC/dev environments, the status code will be 203 instead of 200. So this 203 seems intentional and we don't need to remove it."}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-12-08 02:47:25.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Verified+1

commit_message:
Fix flavor access API ref

Flavor access API ref contain wrong ref for flavor
create,show and list.
They are covered in flavor API ref.

This patch fix above issue.
Closes-Bug: 1523758

Change-Id: I39ebd8ee0c53e1990f64b99c0368275d242d8fb6

commit_message:
Restore info from v2.2 to v2.1

keypairs has microversion support now, but it's not proper to
talk about it in v2.1 doc, we will have microversion doc later, now
we should restore back to v2.1

Change-Id: Ib48bd406dd6be71c0c16b3bc3366ab5af5e92db6
Partial-Bug: #1515222

commit_message:
Allow the volume display_name field to be null

We can create a volume without the display_name.
So the volume resource should allow the display_name to be null.

commit_message:
Improve the validation method about X-Account-Meta-Storlet-Enabled

In storlet_handler middleware, we checks if the account is allowed
to execute Storlets, based on "X-Account-Meta-Storlet-Enabled" metadata.
However, now we only checks whether its value matches "False", so
accounts whose storlet metadata is something like "foo" or even "false"
can execute Storlets.

In this patch, I replace the existing checking with config_true_value
method of swift, and improves the validation logic.

Change-Id: Icce3f76632ee8fabac4c6f7cc6de8d9c11e43126

commit_message:
Refactoring and removing duplicate code of "base.Manager" heirs
without changing the API

This commit does refactoring regarding the base.Manager and the
specific managers that inherit from it (Chassis, Node, Port and
Driver).

The specific managers had a lot of duplicate code in methods like:
get, create, delete and update, they were literally equal, what does
not make sense once we already had the base.Manager inheritance to
avoid this type of problem.

This change moves the duplicate code to the parent (base.Manager) and
make the specific managers simpler by making the base.Manager more
useful regarding code reuse for these methods.

Change-Id: Ic77a86196d5bcd956f0a3ae517200824a4d70aa8
Closes-Bug: #1517631

commit_message:
Fix H405 violations

There are a lot of H405 violation codes.
We need to fix the code for avoiding more violations.

Change-Id: Iaa83626b81a3d8369b16e2b4f394e2bc4628998a
Closes-Bug: #1521899

[{'created': '2015-12-11 11:04:08.000000000', 'message': 'Fix duplicate Image URL validation message

URLField already have a default_validator of URLValidator,
defining another validator appends to the default_validator
causing duplicate message.

We should override the default_validator for restricting the
url schema rather than appending another URLValidator.

Change-Id: Icf09b2a70e63f610e34212ddc4d74f077a07b089
Closes-bug: #1525100
'}]
commit_message:
Fix duplicate Image URL validation message

URLField already have a default_validator of URLValidator,
defining another validator appends to the default_validator
causing duplicate message.

We should override the default_validator for restricting the
url schema rather than appending another URLValidator.

Change-Id: Icf09b2a70e63f610e34212ddc4d74f077a07b089
Closes-bug: #1525100

commit_message:
Adding tests for ng identity basePath constant

This patch improves test coverage for the agular identity
dashboard by adding tests for the basePath constant definition.
A minor consistency issue in the module file is also addressed.

Change-Id: I97d0ce728e44777635bf6590e312fb00d1684582
Partially-Implements: blueprint angularize-identity-tables

commit_message:
[fix-compat] More definitions for oslo.middleware

Please see I04739bc3987786b4bc1fefc70fabaa69b3de52b4 for
context. Adding the modules is not enough. We need
to expose additional classes in the __init__.py for
oslo.middleware package for grenade to work properly

Change-Id: Ib19bcc47909621260902be31eb14e8240155c7d0

commit_message:
Deprecated tox -downloadcache option removed

Caching is enabled by default from pip version 6.0

More info:
https://testrun.org/tox/latest/config.html#confval-downloadcache=path
https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#caching

Change-Id: I1efe914e9665d437afc7fdaf689c64674ea30be1

commit_message:
Use 'service_type' of 'network'. Not 'neutron'

'neutron' is not a 'service_type' in keystone. 'network' is the correct
'service_type' to use.

Closes-Bug: #1525222
Change-Id: I47a41fcb1e6b5ee7c8fb7fd4f895e60d43f36286

commit_message:
Increase Python jobs timeout for Gnocchi

Gnocchi Python jobs runs the whole test suite several time for different
index and storage back-ends, which takes around 40 minutes. This was
picked because having ~6 Python jobs was considered too much.

But the default timeout of 40 minutes is a just and sometimes our job
fails because of that. Let's be generous.

Change-Id: I9999089905d68533531c219c84625d29002665f0

commit_message:
Deprecated tox -downloadcache option removed

Caching is enabled by default from pip version 6.0

More info:
https://testrun.org/tox/latest/config.html#confval-downloadcache=path
https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#caching

Change-Id: Ia7db13132a94d55ebef99fd27bed62f1d75f63b1

commit_message:
Make sure item of policy_dirs is directory

We skip path which was not found in config option policy_dirs, but don't
check if the path is a directory. If path is not directory, a confusing
exception StopIteration,  This commit checks that and raise ValueError
if path is not a directory.

Closes-Bug: #1401302
Change-Id: I7e199987321c528d8f13998020507755a17a2c29

commit_message:
Correct the docstring parameters for PortOpt

The docs for PortOpt are misleading.  The min and max values are
not actually parameters.  They are statically set and do not permit
an override.  Also, the newly added choices parameter is missing
from the doc.

Change-Id: Ie7b03cc85c8e170be5cb7756b01bb3801ca172fa

This patch removes `MANIFEST.in` file as pbr generates a sensible
manifest from git files and some standard files and it removes

commit_message:
Removes MANIFEST.in as it is not needed explicitely by PBR

This patch removes `MANIFEST.in` file as pbr generates a sensible
manifest from git files and some standard files and it removes
the need for an explicit `MANIFEST.in` file.

Change-Id: I47ffde7bca5e4e345544cb930382e711ac79dc3e

commit_message:
Add detailed info to instance and server name

Instance and server name is different from nova perspective, but
end user might don't know it, add more into to both of the fields.

Partial-Bug: #1515222

Use specified client service name for client usage

Create CLIENT_NAME for every client, which can be used to replace seperated
string for service client name.

commit_message:
Revert back to try-with-resources statement

Revert changes that attempted to make sure that DB
connections are closed. The original code used the
java try-with-resources statement which automatically
calls close() on the resource in the try call.

Change-Id: I43be2125e56a93381aa626aea6903a64a9353779

commit_message:
Add Kubernetes podmaster

For HA (http://kubernetes.io/v1.0/docs/admin/high-availability.html)
podmaster need to run at every master node

Change-Id: I48bfb0043dd15b4e76a9c354144786d710e64440
Partially-Implements: blueprint run-kube-as-container

I'm wondering if we need https://review.openstack.org/#/c/256578/ that introduces --serial arg along with this change?

What I mean that we'll have two command line options that we need verify, e.g. what are we going to do if we get:

"--serial --concurrency=8"

do we run in serial mode or use 8 workers?

I think if this feature is going to be implemented, we should not go further the --serial patch (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/256578/) because --concurrency covers all the cases:

--concurrency=X, X>0 translates to "testr run --parallel --concurrency=1, translates to "testr run"
--concurrency=0, translates to "testr run --parallel" (or we could also just pass --concurrency value actually).

I see no value in a separate argument for serial runs provided we can explicitly specify a number of workers.'}, {'account_id': 14356, 'date': '2015-12-11 21:57:09.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2:

commit_message:
The type of number_of_masters should be int not string

number_of_masters, number_of_minions and number_of_nodes
should be number, not string.

Change-Id: Iac20023f0448aab313302c174e3743b95cd42d7a
Closes-Bug: #1524236

commit_message:
retrieve resource with metric only when needed

there appears to be no reason for retrieve resource details
along with metric info when calling get_metrics. this patch
avoids retrieving resource data to minimise query load.

Change-Id: I80c5ed0f6b1c9eef25095048b1fa4dd2b1a7ef90

Looks good, Vinay. 

I have added a comment to address Ryan's question regarding the handling of security group filters on the source side.

Also, the original document was correct w.r.t. the last sentence in the first section. See below.

> All captured packets are forwarded to the mirrors 
> destination port without passing through its outbound
> filters. 

Outbound filters above should be reverted back to inbound filters.

The reason for this is that we want to ensure that the receiving VM (that is connected to the destination port) can see all of the traffic being mirrored from the source ports, irrespective of it's own inbound security group policies. So those inbound filters (for the destination VM) will need to be skipped."}, {'account_id': 11682, 'date': '2014-06-02 19:21:22.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 3:

I think this is a valuable feature. However, I'm not sure I would implement the logical part in this way.

I see port mirroring as something which, from a logical perspective, is much easier.

One idea could have ports characterized as "mirrors" with appropriate attributes, which might include the source port id.

Another idea could be to have a first-level mirror resource, which is then associated with the source port. Nevertheless, since there are use cases where one would like to have mirror ports are regular VIFs probably mirror objects should at the end of the day be associated also with actual ports (the mirror or tap destination).

In any case I'm not convinced by the need for having a tap service top-level resource.

I would like to engage in a constructive discussion on this blueprint, but this would likely mean deferral to K given my pedant and obnoxious attitude.

If you feel that my comments are off topic and just delaying progress, please feel free to ignore them.'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2014-07-14 15:52:21.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 6: Verified+1

In respnose to Salvatore's question...

> It would be good to clarify the intention - that is to 
> say: should this service plugin be part of a
> neutron "core" deployment, or can it be leverage as an
> optional component in a neutron deployment

In my humble opinion, this service plugin should be a part of a core Neutron deployment. One of the most important and obvious role it plays (outside its ability to enable traffic monitoring for security and data analytics) is providing the necessary visibility for troubleshooting network related problems in an OpenStack cloud environment. Tenants who are going about the process of creating complex virtual network topologies and deploying VMs on them, will really appreciate having such a handy debugging aid available (and ready for use) as part of the base Neutron service.

Almost all modern virtual switches provide port mirroring support that is built into their respective feature sets. This service plugin is attempting to offer similar capability for OpenStack tenant virtual networks.'}, {'account_id': 748, 'date': '2014-12-19 02:07:54.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

I personally don't believe that delivering this feature as a service plugin, like the other services, hinders the ability to an operator or a tenant to use it. Can you explain why you think this is?"}, {'account_id': 11578, 'date': '2014-12-19 02:22:46.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

Hi Armando,

From a consumption model point of view, whether the project lives here or there changes very little or nothing, so I think the reasons stated above are fallacious: a user interested in mirroring traffic can very successfully gets his/her hand on this regardless of where it's being developed.

Now, about the question core vs non-core, IMO we need to be very careful about claiming something like this being a fundamental objective of the Neutron mission. I am still on the fence on this, and I suspect I am not alone."}, {'account_id': 261, 'date': '2014-12-19 12:03:01.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

Being "core" and being part of the main source tree (ie: git.openstack.org/openstack/neutron.git) are two very distinct things.

I am not sure if the proposers of this spec claim the need to have the tap service as "core" neutron because they want to stay in the main tree or because they feel like they deserve to be recognised as an "official" openstack effort, or both.

I think both claims could perhaps be revisited, for the benefit of the TAP service itself.

I have no authority in deciding what should be official openstack effort or not, but in the past new additions to the neutron family were always treated as "experimental" for their first release cycle regardless of where the code was pushed (edge firewall still is an experimental effort).
Moreover a recently approved change in governance (which I have not yet fully digested) probably makes this whole discussion unnecessary - you can be officially part of Openstack without having to attach yourself to an integrated program (more here: http://governance.openstack.org/resolutions/20141202-project-structure-reform-spec.html)

Placement of code in different repositories is something that I regard highly beneficials for services which add capabilities to OpenStack networking, as it allows subject matter experts to be fully in control, and have much shorter review cycles compared with those that one would have if the code was in the main neutron tree. 

I understand that this particular work item might have interactions with the l2 agent or that the control plane part is currently entirely implemented within the l2 agent. I am happy to discuss with you ways to do some decoupling there (and have a separate TAP agent); moreover if this spec requires changes to the L2 agent I think there will be no problem in considering this changes and apply all the necessary patches to ensure the TAP service is fully functional.'}, {'account_id': 105, 'date': '2014-12-19 16:22:49.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

DEFERRED UNTIL AFTER KILO

Gerrit isn't the best place to have htis discussion, but here's the reality of where we find ourselves:

1) This spec was submitted on May 28 for Juno, and went through six revisions in a month before it was declined for Juno.
2) The spec was brought back to life on the cusp of the Kilo Spec Proposal Deadline.
3) Consensus was not reached during 12 days of review.

The legality of the situation isn't a question I'm understanding. And you're also missing the key piece: We don't believe TapaaS needs to exist in Neutron, it can exist outside of Neutron. Please read the comments from Salvatore, he's linked a governance change from the TC where they are moving to no longer bless things, and will let anything exist upstream. I'll try to address Alan's comments about Stackforge with the caveat that all I say may be wrong, and it's the vapor of eggnog guiding my fingers:

> What is the Legalities around projects that are pushed to Stackforge, does Openstack cover those projects? 

Stackforge is like github: projects hosted there can pick their favorite license (from the list of OSI approved ones) and choose the regime they prefer for accepting contributions. Most projects in Stackforge default to replicating what existing OpenStack projects do: use Apache Software License 2.0 and enforce the CLA process, enforced in gerrit. Projects hosted on stackforge are not managed/overseen by the OpenStack Technical Committee. I believe the OpenStack trademark can still be applied to projects hosted on stackforge, but the details have to be checked with lawyers, especially after the votes in January.

In the end, your question needs a better definition of 'cover'. I would suggest to move this discussion to the legal-discussion@lists.openstack.org where eggnog has no effect.

> Also, what Neutron projects have been successful to be brought back from stackforge into Neutron/Quantum in the past?

The concept of 'going back' implies that stackforge is some sort of limbo and it's not. Consider that the TC is re-designing how "OpenStack" is defined and that may have a strong impact on what we're discussing here. Again, I would move the conversation on the legal mailing list.'}, {'account_id': 6772, 'date': '2014-12-30 17:59:25.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

I believe Alan's question is more specifically how does it become part of the formal OpenStack release, which is currently being redefined. The existing advanced services (FWaaS, LBaaS, VPNaaS) were already party of Neutron and as such when split out went directly into the openstack namespace.

Newer efforts like group-based-policy and it seems tap-as-a-service are going into the stackforge namespace but will at some point want to move to the openstack namespace. It's unclear (perhaps only to me ;)) what this path will look like with the governance changes currently being proposed."}, {'account_id': 3217, 'date': '2015-01-04 02:52:15.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 8:

We should investigate how the GBP peeps are planning on doing things, given that they have the same set of problems."}, {'account_id': 105, 'date': '2015-02-24 22:37:18.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 8:

commit_message:
Introducing Tap-as-a-Service

This specification aims to add port mirroring capability for tenant
networks in Neutron. The specification covers the description of the
service along with its intended usecase. The specification also includes
the data model and REST API changes.

Implements: blueprint port-mirroring

Change-Id: I087d9d2a802ea39c02259f17d2b8c4e2f6d8d714

commit_message:
Fix the Split button to enable the dropdown toggle

The split button template needs to have the
'dropdown-toggle' directive to allow it to be clicked
to show the menu options.

Co-Authored-By: Kyle Olivo<keolivo@thoughtworks.com>

Change-Id: Id54a915b59d19592dddde390652d4d5513309822
Closes-Bug: #1524115

commit_message:
Change ACLs for stable branches of fuel projects

stable/6.1 and stable/7.0 branches of some fuel-* repos have
exclusive Workflow permissions, this patch adds an option
for change owner to set Workflow -1..+0 which is not inherited from
All-Projects ACL

Change-Id: I58bb6493232b7d6192fac804f169ae5f87b46f47

commit_message:
Enable devstack-plugin-ceph NV jobs for glance and nova

Commit a53859db32475c948ee68ce1f838b20e773b8687 enabled the
devstack-plugin-ceph NV job for cinder only as we didn't
want to load the infra during the Mitaka-1 release rush. This
patch now adds the job to glance and nova projects.

This patch is part of a larger effort of moving the devstack-ceph
CI job from devstack hook -> plugin method.

Change-Id: I6acd66a0a4c43e2af3889928a9751ae3b4993793

commit_message:
split gnocchi tests by indexer to avoid timeouts

we currently have 6 test runs under py27 to handle each combination
of indexer+storage pairs. for each test added, it is run 6 times across
each pair causing it to exceed timeout length.

this patch breaks the tests so we group the tests by indexer so that all
mysql tests are run together and all postgresql tests are run together.

Change-Id: I70b82070fb9f4a4a3a633b000a8eea6240736586

As we just upgraded our codebase to work on Python 3.4, we would
like to make sure that each new patchset pass the tests on both
py27 and py34 environments.

commit_message:
Huawei: Refactor driver for the second time

After a few new features being added into drivers,
we found it hard to maintain the code. For further
working, we need to refactor our code. The work
contains the following:
1. Define a new class, named HuaweiConf, to parse
xml config file. We used an external xml file to
store SAN info. But we do config parsing anywhere
in our code, even two different functions do the
same parsing.
2. Adjust some function structures.
3. Rename some functions & variables.

DocImpact
Implements: blueprint refactor-huawei-driver
Change-Id: I3b8e01e7a5fc1054110cecedf6a17fde3823a885

commit_message:
Move to debug a too verbose log

When a client is gone (died/restart) and somes replies cannot be sent because
the the exchange of this client will never comeback. We log one message per
reply every 0.25 messages during 60 seconds. When the only useful log
is the one where we decide to drop this replies.

This change moves the less important message to debug level.

Change-Id: I508787c0db4dcec2c0027b89eb4e65c4f98022b9
Related-bug: #1524418

Align fuel packages version schema with perestroika

Fuel packages should be aligned to the same versioning schema
as we have in perestroika and specs [1]

[1] https://github.com/openstack/fuel-specs/blob/master/specs/ \
    8.0/separate-mos-from-centos.rst

Closes-bug: #1524758

Change-Id: I1b5bd2617b6d388b2c4852d5f74ae3adf84f8991

commit_message:
Update Object API v1 to spellcheck and make other changes

- Remove passive voice from api-site
- Renamed api-ref/src/wadls/object-api/src/v1/api_samples
  to .../samples
- Renamed code samples using this naming convention:
  <resource>-<action>-request.json or <resource>-<action>-response.json.
  For example, volume-create-request.json and volume-create-response.json.
- Removed unused code samples
- Made method names consistent throughout - use list<resource> for list
  operations, show<resource> for show operations, and so on.

Change-Id: Id2dbc9f35014954bf5b297bd4ebed4d37d0d14f1
Partial-Bug: #1521244

  to .../samples

commit_message:
Report compute-api bugs against nova

For compute-api set the launchpad project users report bugs
against to "nova". Users can report bugs using the "bug icon" that will
directly link to the launchpad project, it currently goes to
"openstack-manuals" which is wrong for this content.

This variable is used by openstackdocstheme 1.2.6.

Closes-Bug: #1524476
Change-Id: I08ba11bb1c5388bc4611cea581274ac5d724c8d9

commit_message:
Only update nodepool images on Tuesdays

Until the regression in tox 2.3.0 is resolved through a new release,
only update nodepool images on Tuesdays so we don't need to delete
them every day (hopefully it will be fixed by Tuesday!).

https://bitbucket.org/hpk42/tox/issues/294

Change-Id: I300857d50c1dc010dba569c5978e45e76a90162c

commit_message:
Fix duplicate auth_section issue

Due to the keystonemiddleware upgrade, now we're running into a
gate failure. This is just a workaround, we will upgrade to
keystoneauth1 soon.

Change-Id: I70517e6a3122b529b9d337dd6472761aedebcf47

commit_message:
improve keystoneclient session initialization

keystoneclient.session.Session.construct() is deprecated, the recommended
way is by using its constructor.

And we should apply http_timeout to the parameter list to improve
robustness.

This patch also extracts those code to a internal function to reduce
duplicate code.

Change-Id: Ia32b056f4b602bd274633780dc0142153e7801b9
Closes-Bug: #1507997

I have started to work on something near to your change. 

We currently enforces keystone V2Password in all openstack clients lib. I t would be cool to allow all auth plugins in Ceilometer.

A new library keystoneauth1 provides helpers methods to construct keystone auth/session that loads the everything from oslo.config.

I have started to replace our ceilometer custom keystone stuffs with this library, The code is bit outdated for now, I will continue to works on this when the next mikita ceilometerclient will be released (with keystoneclient session support). (https://review.openstack.org/#/c/237537/).

commit_message:
using session to construct keystoneclient object

Constructing an instance of the keystoneclient.{v2_0,v3}.client.Client
class without a session is deprecated as of the 1.7.0 release and may
be removed in the 2.0.0 release.

ref: https://github.com/openstack/python-keystoneclient/blob/1.8.1/\
keystoneclient/v2_0/client.py#L140

Change-Id: I62ca50d91ece29628bad310097dec98ab7f8b4cc
Closes-Bug: #1507884

My intention for OPENSTACK_KEYSTONE_DEFAULT_DOMAIN is just for internal value when Horizon is setup to still use single domain.

If we expose this to user, there are two issues:
1. If keystone v3 is running multiple domain, the user would like end-up updating this most of the time.  User from other domain should not know what other domains are used.
2. Domain value should not be shown in login screen, we are exposing internal value publicly to any user.'}, {'account_id': 8040, 'date': '2015-12-08 16:33:31.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1

commit_message:
Add domain initial value on login

Currently there is no default value for
domain field of login form.
This patch add saving last login domain
name into coookies and pre-filling
'Domain' field value on login with
this saved value from cookies.

Closes-Bug: #1523957
Change-Id: Idbbd741358ecabeb51de47cdece662b5019d2092

http://logs.openstack.org/20/255920/1/check/gate-neutron-dsvm-functional/6bf11c8/console.html

I think there needs to be some check to see when neutron-l3 agent starts up properly, just as it is done with wsgi server. At least it may be indicative to some trouble with the agent service startup if we can cap it to 25 secs or so, i.e. with some mechanism to check its up state/proper startup."}]

commit_message:
SIGHUP missed by child daemon process

This issue might be due to the service process missing the
SIGHUP because it is sent too early. This is deduced based
on the logs and code. Since this is not reproducible locally
it is being tried out on the test server.

This is just to test the runs and see the success rate for
test_restart_l3_agent_on_sighup which fails intermittently.

Change-Id: Ief93d46310466d524d251e370abfafce44b6a78e
Closes-Bug: #1518921

commit_message:
Add extensions to $q for resolving all promises

This patch provides an extension service for the $q
service which waits for all promises to settle and then
return which promises fail and which promises pass.

This was a result of having similar looking code in
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/231335/
and
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/234408/

The method name was inspired method which exists in $q
from Kris Oswal but not in the Angular implementation of it.
https://github.com/kriskowal/q/blob/v1/q.js#L1676

Co-Authored-By: Errol Pais<epais@thoughtworks.com>
Co-Authored-By: Kyle Olivo<keolivo@thoughtworks.com>

Change-Id: Ic3d36bba1886e06d7e7aee50c1ddfa17b51a1a65
Partially-Implements: blueprint angularize-images-table

commit_message:
WIP! DO NOT MERGE: refactor DVR local and edge router classes

Rename DVR router classes to distributed and centralized to
reflect their functionality. Refactor code between distributed
router and DvrRouterBase classes to allow the centralized router
class to inherit from DvrRouterBase rather than from the
distributed router class.

TODO: figure out how to instantiate both distributed and
centralized classes when needed and have them coexist correctly

Change-Id: I9356755bd9e54e47e75b6342b702eee31865a538
Signed-off-by: Ryan Moats <rmoats@us.ibm.com>
Closes-Bug: 1458541

    developers. They will give you feedback and may require you to refine it.

    People seldom get their patch approved on the first try, so don't be
    concerned if requested to make corrections. Feel free to modify your patch
    and resubmit a new change-set.

    Patches usually take 3 to 7 days to be reviewed so be patient and be
    available on IRC to ask and answer questions about your work. Also it
    takes generally at least a couple of weeks for cores to get around to
    reviewing code. The more you participate in the community the more
    rewarding it is for you. You may also notice that the more you get to know
    people and get to be known, the faster your patches will be reviewed and
    eventually approved. Get to know others and become known by doing code
    reviews: anybody can do it, and it's a great way to learn the code base.

commit_message:
Add verification for device_owner when missing the port_security attr

port dict extending process will extend the port_security to be True when no
such key found(not use port_sec extension last time). But for port's
device_owner that start with 'network:', like router gateway and dhcp ports,
this attribute should be False.

Related-Bug: 1483315

Change-Id: I20da2214d5a906ca4fe22f5fe391dbb77d9a69db

commit_message:
Fix hardcode for IP Version v4 and v6

In some Neutron code, IPv4 and IPv6 are hardcoded 4 and 6, this patch
using constants which had already defined in neutron/common/constants
module.

Change-Id: I1b16e20a3159405f40c228f60bc458c744a0f0fc

commit_message:
Do not update ACTIVE ports back to BUILD status

Status update (ACTIVE-BUILD-ACTIVE) may trigger a bunch of
unneeded RPC communications between neutron server and l3
dvr agents which may overload server fatally.
Updated ports will be put in PENDING_BUILD status right after
db update to distinguish real port update and cases when agents
are just restarted and syncing with server.

commit_message:
Add API services for Create a Volume, get QoS and tenant limits

Adding cinder services to create and update volumes and volume snapshots,
return Quality of Service and tenant absolute limits.

This is to support dependent patches that will create volumes for Images
from the angular panel for Images.

Co-Authored-By: Errol Pais<epais@thoughtworks.com>
Co-Authored-By: Nathan Zeplowitz<nzeplowi@thoughtworks.com>

Partially-Implements: blueprint angularize-images-table
Change-Id: I4c48c09a0f20f971588b1e920a555f12e7ed4498

commit_message:
Fix "report a bug" launchpad project

For docs set the launchpad project users report bugs
against to "senlin". Users can report bugs
using the "bug icon" that will
directly link to the launchpad project, it currently goes to
"openstack-manuals" which is wrong for this content.

This variable is used by openstackdocstheme 1.2.6.

Also, update comments for the variables passed to
openstackdocstheme.

Change-Id: I15d8cbc4e59b28351f21026f60b1131083540112
Related-Bug: #1524476

commit_message:
add /etc/neutron/rootwrap.d to support devstack

Devstack fails if the rootwrap.d file is missing.
We don't need any rootwrap filters at this time but we need to supply the
file in order to allow Devstack to run successfully.

Change-Id: Ia1fba4b68e7ee341216d57e62176ada969e8e472

commit_message:
Update Orchestration API v1 to spellcheck and make other changes

- Remove passive voice from api-site
- Renamed api-ref/src/wadls/orchestration/src/v1/api_samples
  to .../samples
- Renamed code samples using this naming convention:
  <resource>-<action>-request.json or <resource>-<action>-response.json.
  For example, volume-create-request.json and volume-create-response.json.
- Removed unused code samples
- Made method names consistent throughout - use list<resource> for list
  operations, show<resource> for show operations, and so on.

Change-Id: I9fe99fa541e52117b43c116d1e0a6095f9b8ca87
Partial-Bug: #1521244

commit_message:
Remove Cassandra repository for MidoNet element

After testing and modifying puppet-tripleo to use locp-cassandra instead
of midonet-cassandra,

https://review.openstack.org/#/c/251319/

we don't need to clone this module anymore.

commit_message:
Retype functionality in Tintri driver

At this point default retype behavior is as follows. If a volume changes
type on the same backend then that volume will be migrated. Since Tintri
VMstore does not differentiate between volume types, we can avoid this
migration by implementing retype functionality.

Change-Id: I40b28327e13821d6fb45f89b15267b21ed4c2e8c
closes-bug: 1524435

commit_message:
Added constraints tox targets

These are eventually going to be used in gate instead of unconstrained
jobs. There is some code duplication in commands definitions, but tox
does not allow to inherit definitions with {posargs} substitution.

Made tox_install.sh use constraints file to install both the project
and neutron dependency, if the first argument is 'constrained'.

Change-Id: I699022b285594edf3c5db10fbdac2f904dc42928
Partial-Bug: #1522503
Depends-On: I7d43cf950ec9c337da991b1e765b13743c4e18c2

revisions:
[{'created': '2015-06-09 21:26:39.000000000', 'message': "Add address scope to ports in RPC response to L3 agent

The L3 agent needs to know the address scope of each port of each
router it sets up in order to enforce isolation between scopes.
Neutron doesn't yet have a first class address scope, that will be
added by a different patch [1].  However, subnet pools are already
defined and can be treated as address scopes already.  This means that
the RPC changes can be defined and allow the L3 agent changes to be
developed indepently of the first class address scope support in the
Neutron server.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/189741/

Change-Id: I6a7b3708fadefff1919d70ab1b8bc345b3fbe81c
Partially-Implements: blueprint address-scopes
"}, {'created': '2015-06-12 17:30:25.000000000', 'message': "Add address scope to ports in RPC response to L3 agent

The L3 agent needs to know the address scope of each port of each
router it sets up in order to enforce isolation between scopes.
Neutron doesn't yet have a first class address scope, that will be
added by a different patch [1].  However, subnet pools are already
defined and can be treated as address scopes already.  This means that
the RPC changes can be defined and allow the L3 agent changes to be
developed indepently of the first class address scope support in the
Neutron server.

commit_message:
Add address scope to ports in RPC response to L3 agent

The L3 agent needs to know the address scope of each port of each
router it sets up in order to enforce isolation between scopes.

This commit adds a devref for the address scopes and subnet pools
features.

Change-Id: I6a7b3708fadefff1919d70ab1b8bc345b3fbe81c
Partially-Implements: blueprint address-scopes

(1 comment)

I'm not against this, I just have a question inline that I want to make sure a core looks at.

You're right that we need to make a change along these lines.  The deprecation Julien is talking about is here: https://github.com/openstack/oslo.utils/blob/ac0e28b4d83c35e86e493e8f472537b4127b0c7e/oslo_utils/timeutils.py#L72

I just wonder whether we need to go with using .strftime() instead with a specific format string instead of using .isotime(), because it looks like .isotime() is going to change way time is displayed in some API responses."}, {'account_id': 1669, 'date': '2015-12-04 15:09:57.000000000', 'content': "Patch Set 1:

commit_message:
Replace oslo_utils.timeutils

This change introduces glance.common.timeutils that provides the
timeutils previously consumed from oslo_utils.

Oslo is deprecating some timeutils functionality which of Glance
depends on. Suggested replacement (isoformat) would break glance APIs
so it's cleaner to carry this functionality in Glance rather than
re-invent the wheel.

Co-Authored-By: Erno Kuvaja <jokke@usr.fi>
Co-Authored-By: Sabari Kumar Murugesan <smurugesan@vmware.com>

Change-Id: I91e1cc9a273249fd88749cecf21200f3f5e2bab1

commit_message:
Add SIGHUP handlers for compute rpcapi to console and conductor

This adds SIGHUP handlers to console, consoleauth, and conductor
services to reload the compute_rpcapi. This is required for auto
version pinning to be dynamic at runtime.

Related to blueprint service-version-behavior

Change-Id: I83a25bda681daa249ffca8bc1f38edcd70dd7cc5

[{'created': '2015-12-11 15:16:01.000000000', 'message': "create apt_get_update to try to work around broken mirrors

Ubuntu's apt mirroring mechanism produces inconsistent mirrors pretty
regularly. The devstack-gate apt-get update model seems to have been
more effective getting past this than what we did in devstack. Adopt
that method for our updates.

Change-Id: I97c7896ef38b275aacb4f933fc849acee1bab858
(cherry picked from commit 88ee8ce4684e13865123636dd5d2baa5d6a44ef7)
"}]
commit_message:
create apt_get_update to try to work around broken mirrors

Ubuntu's apt mirroring mechanism produces inconsistent mirrors pretty
regularly. The devstack-gate apt-get update model seems to have been
more effective getting past this than what we did in devstack. Adopt
that method for our updates.

Change-Id: I97c7896ef38b275aacb4f933fc849acee1bab858
(cherry picked from commit 88ee8ce4684e13865123636dd5d2baa5d6a44ef7)

commit_message:
Removes MANIFEST.in as it is not needed explicitely by PBR

This patch removes `MANIFEST.in` file as pbr generates a sensible
manifest from git files and some standard files and it removes
the need for an explicit `MANIFEST.in` file.

Change-Id: I38b985cc915cbccfa6ba83ae0cffbd72128f146e

commit_message:
Deprecated tox -downloadcache option removed

Caching is enabled by default from pip version 6.0

More info:
https://testrun.org/tox/latest/config.html#confval-downloadcache=path
https://pip.pypa.io/en/stable/reference/pip_install/#caching

Change-Id: Ic89af2a7dd05629a00a9dd4857866f6028afc9d5

commit_message:
Add admonition to telemetry code

This code is subject to change in the near future.  The alarm
class is probably moving out of here and many of the resource
property have aliases.  We have agreed not to support the old
aliases going forward, because it doesn't work well.  The
admonition can be pulled after these issues are fixed.

Closes-Bug: #1468086
Change-Id: Ica464a6c1e2281f4acbd25a121a399b6b0c81376

commit_message:
Decompose OFAgent mechanism driver from neutron tree completely

All 3rd-party code is required to be removed from the neutron tree.
This change removes definition for ofagent mechanism driver from
neutron repository.

Change-Id: Ia21387eeaed71f38822356e22e4adbd237c1e64c
Closes-Bug: #1524164
Depends-On: I04c741daf12e7628e2c1e2d1b81b2b2ce1310542

Our delete APIs return True if the delete succeeded, or False if
the thing being deleted was not found. delete_object() was not doing

commit_message:
Bug fix: delete_object() returns True/False

Our delete APIs return True if the delete succeeded, or False if
the thing being deleted was not found. delete_object() was not doing
this, so this makes it consistent with the other delete API calls.

Also adds missing unit tests for this method.

Change-Id: I0951765193459300f08b0ab804e6ca327c6fa57d

OK. Here is the issue... as part of configure_for_func_testing.sh, you want to run an oslo.config package. However, all the requirements files are installed as part of the tox.ini run, which happens AFTER this script runs.

You need to install the oslo.config package as part of the configure_for_func_testing.sh processing (right after the call to configure_host_for_func_testing, which sets up most dependencies and packages). I think you may be able to leverage off of the install_package method that gets pulled in from neutron's configure_for_func_testing.sh, which pulls it in from devstack. commit_message:
Automatically generate neutron VPNaaS configuration files

This adds a new tox environment, genconfig, which generates sample
neutron VPNaaS configuration file using oslo-config-generator.

Updates to some configuration option help messages to reflect useful
details that were missing in the code but were present in config files.

DocImpact: Update the docs that VPNaaS no longer includes static example
configuration files. Instead, use tools/generate_config_file_samples.sh
to generate them and the files generated now end with .sample extension.

Partially-Implements: blueprint autogen-neutron-conf-file

Change-Id: I4a6094b8218dfd320d05bfb1e3bc121e8930c551
Partial-bug: #1199963

commit_message:
Updated oslo.db to 4.1.0

New version of oslo.db is needed in Nova for enginefacade.
New annotation 'allow_async' from oslo.db needed in this
patch I339a50e53652e5690ece33ee711fbea2cca61f65.

Change-Id: I5e49bf8e178f5ded04b68589f36858f693db7b69

I've been guilty of the same in some of the Service JS I've written. I'm not sure if a default Toast to show it always is a good idea.

I'm quite in favor of doing suppressError in all API's and leave the error handling where the invocation happens."}, {'account_id': 17013, 'date': '2015-11-19 07:12:43.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Patch Set 1 was rebased'}, {'account_id': 3, 'date': '2015-11-19 08:05:41.000000000', 'content': 'Patch Set 2: Verified+1

commit_message:
Correct the host field of instance metadata

Fow now, the 'host' field of instance resource medata is instance.hostId,
which is a hash string based on project id and hypervisor name, it is
hard to indicate which host the instance running on. This change add a new
instance metadata field "instance_host" to indicate the hostname of the
host the instance running on.

Change-Id: Iaa6fa9ef099f617da30cc7af74aa74a845064489
Closes-Bug: #1506610

commit_message:
Implements groupby for statistics API

Queries for metrics to obtain all dimensions
before quering for statistics with merge_metrics
as False, which returns response with dimensions.

The statistics response with dimensions is used to
perform in-memory computations based on the groupby
dimension. Only a single groupby is supported.

The current implementation is memory-intensive and
can be improved further to constrain memory usage.
This patch is an initial step in that direction.

Change-Id: I98ad72337ed50b2f6703afc2e7c4e4689590b2c7

commit_message:
Handles input aggregate for statistics

When statistics API is used with custom
aggregates as input, there is an attribute
error in client as it expects an aggregate
dict in response.

This adds the aggregate dict in response
when input has an aggregate function.

Change-Id: Ide13f5d16b6e4ef11cdcb9c98d85200efaf0cb91

commit_message:
Fixes statistics API when timestamp is specified

When timestamp/timestamp range is specified,
statistics API fails because timestamps are not
being converted to ISO 8601 formatted times, also
when parsing the response, the timezone offsets are
not being dropped.

Monasca API expects timestamps in ISO 8601 format
and ceilometer statistics API expects timestamp in
response in a timezone-naive format.

This patch fixes that so that statistics API works
when timestamps are specified in input filter.

Change-Id: I67055a661478fc15a06c3714f431c484f303658c

commit_message:
Add cmd_resource option to NeutronClient.resolve

This option needs to be added to the NeutronClient _resolve method
to allow for resolving multiple version of resources which are not
compatible.

For example, the lbaas v1 pool and lbaas v2 pools are incompatible,
and must be differentiated when making requests. The v1 pool can be
found without specifying any cmd_resource, while the v2 pool will
need cmd_resource to be set to 'lbaas_pool'.

Blueprint: lbaasv2-suport

Change-Id: Id6b4ab7a56b6a6339263dd45363b0867b46777fa

[{'created': '2015-12-09 09:01:02.000000000', 'message': 'Fix a response code for show object metadata

When show object metadata succeeded, the response code is 200 but
api-ref description is 204. So this patch fixes the response code
from 204 to 200.

Change-Id: If98ca9975a7c39217116d94d98bf6bc16be28bc2
Closes-Bug: #1524159
'}]
commit_message:
Fix a response code for show object metadata

When show object metadata succeeded, the response code is 200 but
api-ref description is 204. So this patch fixes the response code
from 204 to 200.

Change-Id: If98ca9975a7c39217116d94d98bf6bc16be28bc2
Closes-Bug: #1524159

The per test pages were fixing the run_time value to 2 decimal places,
this was likely in an attempt to make the any written numbers be more
concise and readable. However when graphing the data, doing truncation
like that on the values makes things just look weird. Since we're not
actually printing any numbers we can just drop this. If we do need to

commit_message:
Don't fix run_time to 2 decimal places

The per test pages were fixing the run_time value to 2 decimal places,
this was likely in an attempt to make the any written numbers be more
concise and readable. However when graphing the data, doing truncation
like that on the values makes things just look weird. Since we're not
actually printing any numbers we can just drop this. If we do need to
render text with the run_times in the future we can just do the
truncation in the html.

Change-Id: I467513cc62b6605ac3f8d1719bf042b133f14116

commit_message:
Split neutron tasks for task-based deployment

This commit wraps up tasks definitions for
neutron to be able to run several tasks in
orchestrated cross-node mode. This commit
is compatible with both tasks format.

This commit runs primary-.* tasks on primary
controller and others on non primary-cnt nodes
thus doing the same job as role-based deployment
does.

It has been tested against neutron VLAN scenario
and passed required tests at the custom environment
with task-based deployment

Change-Id: I8ede075c35c25aeb8a5957e7a10dcd2a2804413a
Implements: blueprint task-based-deployment-astute

commit_message:
Change nova-compute upgrade level to auto

As part of upgrade process we need new services to detect what is the oldest
version running on compute nodes.

Change-Id: Id65f2bc765828054bf5d5562de27255031254821
Partially-Implements: blueprint upgrade-nova
